&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git" rel="external" target="_blank">Git&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> is a distributed version control system. It&amp;rsquo;s free software created by Linus Torvalds, the creator of the Linux kernel, and distributed under GNU GPL version 2.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Installation and Configuration of an SVN Repository</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Installation_et_configuration_d%5C%27un_repository_SVN/</link><pubDate>Fri, 06 Jul 2012 14:40:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Installation_et_configuration_d%5C%27un_repository_SVN/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>If you want to use &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subversion_(software)" rel="external" target="_blank">Subversion&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>, the successor of CVS, you first need to install Apache 2.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="installation">Installation &lt;a href="#installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Here are the packages to install:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>CVS Installation and Configuration</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Installation_et_configuration_de_CVS/</link><pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2008 18:57:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Installation_et_configuration_de_CVS/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="installation">Installation &lt;a href="#installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;h3 id="debian">Debian &lt;a href="#debian" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="17688ac" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>apt-get install cvs xinetd&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h3 id="red-hat">Red Hat &lt;a href="#red-hat" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="3f2221f" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>up2date cvs&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="creating-admin-group-and-directories">Creating Admin Group and Directories &lt;a href="#creating-admin-group-and-directories" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="1d5b93f" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>adduser cvsadmin
mkdir -p /home/cvsadmin/repository
mkdir /home/cvsadmin/.lock
chown -Rf :cvsadmin /home/cvsadmin
chmod -Rf 775 /home/cvsadmin
chmod -Rf 777 /home/cvsadmin/.lock
ln -s /home/cvsadmin/repository /usr/local/cvsroot&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="repository-initialization">Repository Initialization &lt;a href="#repository-initialization" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="9e8274c" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>export CVSROOT=/usr/local/cvsroot
cvs -d $CVSROOT init
chown -Rf root:cvsadmin /home/cvsadmin/repository/* &amp;amp;&amp;amp; chmod -Rf 777 /home/cvsadmin/repository/*&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="activating-lock-files">Activating Lock Files &lt;a href="#activating-lock-files" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>To ensure that lock files are stored in a directory writable by all, you need to modify the &lt;code>/usr/local/cvsroot-backup/CVSROOT/config&lt;/code> file as follows:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>CVS: Using CVS</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/CVS_:_Utilisation_de_CVS/</link><pubDate>Sun, 20 May 2007 20:37:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/CVS_:_Utilisation_de_CVS/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;strong>CVS&lt;/strong>, an acronym for &lt;strong>Concurrent Versions System&lt;/strong>, is free software (GPL license) for version management, successor to SCCS. Although it is still widely used in the open source software domain, it is now obsolete with the arrival of its successor Subversion. Since it helps sources converge towards the same destination, we say that CVS manages concurrent versions. It can function both in command line mode and through a graphical interface. It consists of client modules and one or more server modules for exchange areas.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>SVK: Creating a Read-Only Mirror for SVN</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/SVK_:_Cr%C3%A9er_un_mirroir_en_lecture_pour_SVN/</link><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2007 22:32:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/SVK_:_Cr%C3%A9er_un_mirroir_en_lecture_pour_SVN/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="svk-creating-a-read-only-mirror-for-svn">SVK: Creating a Read-Only Mirror for SVN &lt;a href="#svk-creating-a-read-only-mirror-for-svn" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Here is a short but useful guide for creating a read-only mirror of an SVN repository:&lt;/p>
